727782f-a.title: Queens: Queens Boulevard - 82nd Avenue
727782f-a.text:
Queens Boulevard, west side, between 82nd Road and 82nd Avenue, showing Muller's Gold Fish Pond. The old boundary line between Newton and Jamaica passed through this pond. Mr. Armbruster states that it was located near Peter Opper's Hotel, on the south side of 82nd Avenue, just west of the Boulevard.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  July 17, 1897

727781f-b.title: Queens: Queens Boulevard - 82nd Avenue
727781f-b.text:
Queens Boulevard, east side, from 8End Avenue to Union Turnpike, showing, under construction, the new Cueens Borough Hall on property formerly belonging to Sarah Palmer. It was opened December 44, 1940. View 1 fs north from 82nd Avenue; view 2, south from Union Turnpike; and view 3 shows the rear, seenTfn-point east on the Turnpike. For additional data see

725668f-a.text:

726612f-a.title: Queens: Queens Boulevard - 82nd Avenue
726612f-a.text:
Flushing Meadow Park (2ueens): A general view north across the Flushing meadows from Cueens Boulevard, at 82nd Avenue, showing the site of the New York World's Fair 1939-40. Note the car yards of the Independent System Subway, at the lower end of the
park.
Vtew 2 is northeastward across the artificially created lakes, which later became part of the Fair's amusement center,
from Grand Central Parkway and 76th Road.
View 1: Sune 29, 1936
View 2: February 10, 1937
P. L. Sperr
